Vets shouldn’t have to worry about how to get to their health care appointments, but too often travel is a real burden, especially for vets in rural communities. Today, I joined @MacTXPress to introduce bipartisan leg to help rural vets get to & from their appts more easily.

Yesterday, the House passed the #SAFEBanking Act, a bipartisan bill I cosponsored that applies federal banking laws to legal marijuana businesses in Washington state and across the U.S. to improve public safety, transparency and accountability.
Right now, legitimate cannabis-related businesses in Washington state are often forced to operate on a cash-only basis, harming business and increasing risks.
